 states and look at the correlation.
 He said this is a new result because in continuous variables, you're doing
 something you do with unitaries and spins.
 The math is nearly the same but the physical situations vastly different.
 Plus he said he hasn't quite seen it before.
 A little search on the net seems to support his claim.
\end_layout

