\begin_layout Itemize
Eigenket
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Derived the result using a slightly different approach.
 Instead of requiring both eigenkets to be equal, I constructed the ket
 to be an eigenket of modular momentum and then demanded it is an eigenket
 for modular position, to fix the coefficients.
 This did it.
 The result is 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\bar{x},\bar{p}\right\rangle =\sum_{n}e^{in\bar{x}\left(\frac{2\pi}{L}\right)}\left|\bar{p}+\frac{nh}{L}\right\rangle $
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Analogously one can start with 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\bar{x}+nL\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 and obtain an expression.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
To prove they are the same, I took the fourier transform of these as 
\begin_inset Formula $\int e^{i\bar{p}x}dx$
\end_inset

 in the position space and upto constant scaling factors, the result was
 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{\frac{i\bar{p}\bar{x}}{\hbar}}$
\end_inset

 which proves nothing I just realized.
 I must do this for an arbitrary 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and not for 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{p}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
I also wrote a small matlab code [projectSiegen/simplerPlots]
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Need to fix the x axis after fft: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/13397393/uni
t-of-fftdft-x-axis, http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4364823/how-do-i-obtain-th
e-frequencies-of-each-value-in-a-fft/4371627#4371627
\end_layout

