\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xm93utUP7YE&list=PLOy5dvWSc5d5mGF4hr0D3j4G0AZFTkVv
s&index=8 | hilarious, and has gotten me to start liking Bohmian mechanics.
 Together with yesterday's seminar (that suggested that the consequence
 of Bell's prediction is that locality is violated), it seems like the way
 to go.
 While on the other hand, it is almost like Newton saying how can gravity
 act at a distance and Einstein coming up with a mechanism.
