\begin_layout Itemize
It turns out that it is almost trivial to evaluate this also.
 The answer is 
\begin_inset Formula $W(q,p)\sim e^{iZ(q-L/2)\phi}e^{ipL/\hbar}$
\end_inset

 upto some signs.
 So it is well behaved and bounded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Surprisingly though, if I don't use the anti-commutation, I get 
\begin_inset Formula $W(q,p)\sim e^{iZ(q-L/2)\phi/2}e^{ipL/\hbar}e^{iZ(q+L/2)\phi/2}$
\end_inset

 which is obviously not the same as the previous statement.
 I'll stick to this because to derive the commutation, I had to make some
 assumptions which I'm not so sure hold.
 [Later: It is infact the same as I'll discover next week]
\end_layout

